page.title: 01INTRODUCTION
page.content: The area is almost all countryside approximately fifty per cent open land and fifty per cent wooded.There are twenty-two seperate woods and four coppices.There are also twelve farms.There is very little housing in the area and what there is tends to be large detached properties.Apart from a small caravan park there are three public houses,one school and one church in the area. The block is directly south of Beaconsfield and west of Wooburn Green.It is mainly high ground,undulating in nature.
